<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="mb-5">
      <h1 class="title">About Rooted in Winnipeg</h1>
      <p class="subtitle is-5 mb-2">
        A Winnipeg plant shop concept built as a full-stack Rails e-commerce project.
      </p>
      <p>
        This project represents a local business moving from in-store sales to an online storefront,
        with an emphasis on realistic product data, clear customer flows, and reliable order records.
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="message is-primary">
      <div class="message-header">
        <h2 class="is-size-6 has-text-weight-semibold has-text-white">Storefront Features</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Product catalog browsing with category navigation, filtering, and search</li>
          <li>Session cart with quantity updates and checkout review</li>
          <li>Customer accounts and order history pages</li>
          <li>Province-based tax calculation during checkout</li>
          <li>Stripe-hosted payment flow for final order payment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="message is-info">
      <div class="message-header">
        <h2 class="is-size-6 has-text-weight-semibold has-text-white">Data Integrity and Model Design</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Products belong to categories and include botanical details from real seed data</li>
          <li>Users are linked to provinces to support GST/PST/HST tax logic</li>
          <li>Orders keep immutable subtotal, tax, and total snapshots</li>
          <li>Order items store unit price snapshots for historical accuracy</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="message is-link">
      <div class="message-header">
        <h2 class="is-size-6 has-text-weight-semibold has-text-white">Seed Data Source</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Plant records are sourced from the Perenual API</li>
          <li>Categories and Canadian province tax rates are seeded in-app</li>
          <li>A <code>PERENUAL_API_KEY</code> is required for full product seeding</li>
          <li>Fallback values keep seed runs stable when API fields are incomplete</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
